Title: Koni Classic Red Dampers Front Left Shock Absorber 8040-1087 for Buick Century Saloon (70 - 77)
Content: The world famous Koni Sport Damper is the flagship of the Koni damper portfolio. Simply referred to as 'Koni Yellows' by car enthusiasts, they are the number one choice for fast road driving. Koni use the same high quality parts in these Koni Sport Dampers as they use with the professionals out on the racetrack. The result is a damper that offers the ultimate in shock absorber technology - better road holding, less chassis movement and unlimited performance & safety. All Koni Sport dampers are rebound adjustable, so you can adjust the rebound damping force to suit your particular driving style or road surface. In fact many Koni Sport dampers can be adjusted whilst the shocks are still on the car, so you can fine tune to your heart's content! These Koni Sport dampers are perfect to use with lowering springs - you can lower your car up to 40mm. Any more than this would cause damage to the shock absorber.
Short Description: * Adjustment Method : (ON CAR) Externally Top Adjustable * Front Damper Construction : Twin Tube Gas Hydraulic * with these KONI Sport dampers the car can be lowered approx. 20 mm (Clipped Spring Seat)
Image Title: Koni Classic Red Dampers Front Left Shock Absorber 8040-1087 for Buick Century Saloon (70 – 77)

Title: Golf VI MK6 Excl. GTI, 4-Motion & DCC Susp. 55 mm only
Content: Koni STR.T dampers combine Koni quality, performance and technical know how with an unbelievable price tag! With Koni STR.T you are still benefiting from perfect road holding and optimum handling, but without the ability to adjust the rebound damping level of your suspension. Koni set the damping rate using their long standing motorsport experience. This kit contains a full set of Koni STR.T dampers and a set of perfectly matched H&R Sports Lowering Springs.
Short Description: Lowers Front by 35mm, and Rear by 35mm Fits models with a front axle load from 981 kg up to 1020 kg The amount of lowering will be reduced on vehicles fitted with original (OEM) sport suspension. The lowering of the front axle depends on the vehicle specification and weight of the engine. All wheel/tyre combinations are allowed which have been approved by the ABE or other certified wheel testing institutes (Germany, Austria, Switzerland). Price is for a full car set of shocks and springs

Title: 156 Saloon 1.6 16V, 1.8 16V, 2.0 16V
Content:
Koni Special-Active - The Seemingly Impossible Realised. The next generation of premium shock absorbers that offer superior handling without compromise.

These Koni Special-Active Shock Absorbers recognise the road condition and your driving style and adjust themselves to provide the best ride and damper experience. You will find that your car will be more responsive and the ride will be smoother over imperfect road surfaces. Handling, comfort and grip will all improve with Special-Active.

Koni performed extensive drive tests on cars equipped with OEM / Koni STRT / Koni Sport / Koni Heavy Track shock absorbers on the front axle and Special-Active shock absorbers on the rear axle and vice versa, and found that the positive effects of the Active technology were very noticeable in all combinations. Therefore using these shocks on only 1 axle instead of mounting a full car set of 4 pieces is absolutely no problem! As with all Koni shocks, they must be fitted in axle sets (both left and right). This Kit comes with a match set of APEX Sports Springs. *Lowering of over 40mm is not recommended on Special Active dampers as this can damage the valve within the unit which make the able to react to road conditions and driving style.
Short Description:
• Front Lowering : 35mm
  • Rear Lowering : 35mm
  • The amount of lowering will be reduced on vehicles if fitted with Original Sport Suspension/OEM. Ie BMW M-Tech, Audi Sportline etc
  • The lowering of the front axle depends on the vehicle specification and weight of the engine.
  • All wheel/tire combinations are allowed which have been approved by the ABE or other certified Wheel Testing Institutes (Germany, Austria, Switzerland).
  • Excludes self-leveling.

Title: Koni GTS Coilovers Kit 1200-1001 for A3 8V FWD Cabriolet 1.0TFSi 2014 - 2019
Content:
Koni GTS Coilover Kit

With a history developed in Formula 1 racing, KONI knows how to maximize the control of your suspension setup. KONI GTS coilover suspension kits combine world-class KONI Sport adjustable valving, linear lowering springs, ride height adjustable perches, and threaded bodies. A full kit ready to install on your car.

Made for both on road driving and weekend track days, the GTS range offers the user a fully customizable suspension package – ride height adjustable and valving adjustable – allowing a wide range of suspension setups from one kit. Look stylish with maximum suspension practicality with KONI GTS.
  • KONI DNA in a stylish coilover setup, with world-class Sport adjustable technology.
  • Both ride height and valving adjustability.
  • Full kit, including top mount, ready to install.
  • Dual purpose for on road and on the track.
  • Perfect for amateur motor enthusiast.
Short Description:
• Incl. S-Line suspension
  • Front: for original struts 55 mm only
  • Rear: only for cars with multi-link suspension
  • Vehicles With Magnetic Ride/DDC require a delete kit which is not supplied
  • Front Lowering : 40-60mm Rear Lowering : 35-70mm
Image Title: Koni GTS Coilover Kit 1200-1001 for Audi A3 8V 2WD Cabrio 1.0TFSi 2014 - 2019

KONI GTS coilover suspension kits combine world-class KONI Sport adjustable valving, linear lowering springs, ride height adjustable perches, and threaded bodies. A full kit ready to install on your car.

Made for both on road driving and weekend track days, the GTS range offers the user a fully customizable suspension package – ride height adjustable and valving adjustable – allowing a wide range of suspension setups from one kit. Look stylish with maximum suspension practicality with KONI GTS.
  • KONI DNA in a stylish coilover setup, with world-class Sport adjustable technology.
  • Both ride height and valving adjustability.
  • Full kit, including top mount, ready to install.
  • Dual purpose for on road and on the track.
  • Perfect for amateur motor enthusiast.

Title: Test - Alfa Romeo 156 Saloon 4 cyl models, excl. 1.9JTD
Content:
The next generation of premium shock absorbers that offer superior handling without compromise. It is the latest advancement in the KONIproduct portfolio. Utilizing the most recent generation of KONI’s patented Frequency Selective Damping technology, it controls large body motions and cornering forces but smooths expansion joints and rough roads for improved comfort.
Two characteristics that seemed diametrically- opposed, proved to be a source of inspiration for specialists from KONI. Following lengthy development and testing, the ultimate solution was reached: KONI FSD – Frequency Selective Damping.

A revolutionary technique whereby the benefits of both types of ride characteristics are combined in one perfect shock absorber. Banishing the disadvantages of the past. Special-Active shock absorbers; a smart suspension system adjusting automatically to road conditions as well as driving style. And all of this in a fraction of a second. Special-Active guarantees greater stability, greater control and thus greater driving pleasure. Koni Special-Active dampers are used by many vehicle manufacturers to enhance the suspension of their top models, these include, Mercedes, Alfa Rome, Abarth, Vauxhall/Opel and even Lamborghini.

To learn more about how the FSD feature in each damper works, click here.
